headlines.description: — Even though he tied a career high by scoring 31 points before halftime, Jayson Tatum wasn't tempted to chase a huge number.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 41 points, Celtics beat Nets 118-110 for 5th straight win

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Jalen Williams scored 33 points, Shai Gilgeous-Alexander added 32 points and five assists and Oklahoma City shook off a sluggish start beat the Orlando Magic 127-113 on Tuesday night in the Thunder's final game before the All-Star break.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Williams, Shai Gilgeous-Alexander lead Thunder past Magic 127-113

headlines.description: — Nikola Jovic kept on working and waiting for his chance even as he struggled to earn playing time over the last few weeks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jovic scores career-high 24, Adebayo gets triple-double as Heat beat Bucks 123-97 without Butler

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 28 points, Devin Booker added 25 and the Phoenix Suns outlasted the Sacramento Kings 130-125 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Durant scores 28, Devin Booker adds 25, Suns outlast Kings 130-125

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards didn't think he could play against the Trail Blazers. Then he scored 41 points.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards has 41 and the Timberwolves win the first of 2 against the Blazers 121-109

events.name: Detroit Pistons at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 25 points and eight assists, Anthony Davis had 20 points and 14 rebounds, and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the NBA-worst Detroit Pistons 125-111 Tuesday night for their fifth win in six games.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron, Davis lead surging Lakers past Pistons 125-111 for their 5th victory in 6 games
